snippet.textDisplay:
When i was child i always used to mock this song and cry out loud this line "Mujhe se pahli si muhabat mera mahboob na maang" and then I used to criticize the poet that he is weak person that he can't love his beloved.

Now i have grown up and get to know what Faiz sahab try to portrait through these lines and what love he was talking about. 

مجھ سے پہلی سی محبت مری محبوب نہ مانگ 
میں نے سمجھا تھا کہ تو ہے تو درخشاں ہے حیات 
تیرا غم ہے تو غم دہر کا جھگڑا کیا ہے 
تیری صورت سے ہے عالم میں بہاروں کو ثبات 
تیری آنکھوں کے سوا دنیا میں رکھا کیا ہے 
تو جو مل جائے تو تقدیر نگوں ہو جائے 
یوں نہ تھا میں نے فقط چاہا تھا یوں ہو جائے 
اور بھی دکھ ہیں زمانے میں محبت کے سوا 
راحتیں اور بھی ہیں وصل کی راحت کے سوا 
ان گنت صدیوں کے تاریک بہیمانہ طلسم 
ریشم و اطلس و کمخاب میں بنوائے ہوئے 
جا بہ جا بکتے ہوئے کوچہ و بازار میں جسم 
خاک میں لتھڑے ہوئے خون میں نہلائے ہوئے 
جسم نکلے ہوئے امراض کے تنوروں سے 
پیپ بہتی ہوئی گلتے ہوئے ناسوروں سے 
لوٹ جاتی ہے ادھر کو بھی نظر کیا کیجے 
اب بھی دل کش ہے ترا حسن مگر کیا کیج

snippet.textDisplay: What have you done first Ali Sethi sung "ranjish hi sahi"  in his sweet voice with out paying any attention to the lyrics. now just when the poem started to imprent its effect on the mind ("Khak main lithery hoey Khoon main nehlaye hoe") you handed over the vocals to Humaira when it was ("Lot jati hai udher ko bhi nazar kya kijye") supposed to be sung by the same singer(nabel). and This just break the effect of the poem.   this was not expected from Bilal Maqsood Man you are from Literary family. I mean I was not expecting it to be at the same level as of Madam noor jahan. But you should consider the context of the lyrics as well especially in poems Because some time its the context that only matters unlike a ""ghazal" where every "sheher" has its own identity... It was really distasteful after the fact it was well composed and beautifully sung. but please consider the context of the lyrics in poems. and pronunciation in Ghazals. By the way Faiz Dedicated this poem To Madam Noor Jahan and never recite it in any "gathering"  after She sang it.

snippet.textDisplay: Pakistan ka Matlab Kiya ...for me it has always  been  Ahmed Faraz, Faiz, Noor Jehan, Mehdi Hasan and Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan and now the Studio . I would have been dead if Coke had messed up my favorite Nazam of Faiz Sahib sung by Noor Jehan. I am elated that Humera can still demand my love and affection and Nabeel has made all Malakwal area proud  because of Shaukat Ali,   his father 's respect and his contributions to music of Punjab and we are so proud that someone so young can sing w such eloquence and authority and ease  a very complex nazam with very complicated urdu and persian poetry. So my salute to Mekaal my all time favorite one man sufi music studio...I can't describe that finally somebody did a cover that we can proud of...This is so far the third song  of season 10 that will live forever. So Balal and Maqsood  I forgive you for Sayouni...you have done wonderful job this year.
